President Muhammadu Buhari and Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo on Saturday attended the 2022 Armed Forces Remembrance Day. The event which takes place every January 15 to honour the fallen heroes was held in Abuja. Other dignitaries at the event include Ahmad Lawan, senate president; Femi Gbajabiamila, speaker of the house of representatives, and Boss Mustapha, secretary to government of the federation. Below are photos. <img class="alignnone wp-image-650156" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/2022-ARMED-FORCES-REMEMBRANCE-DAY15.jpg" alt="" width="550" height="367" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/2022-ARMED-FORCES-REMEMBRANCE-DAY15.jpg 1080w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/2022-ARMED-FORCES-REMEMBRANCE-DAY15-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/2022-ARMED-FORCES-REMEMBRANCE-DAY15-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/2022-ARMED-FORCES-REMEMBRANCE-DAY15-768x512.jpg 768w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/2022-ARMED-FORCES-REMEMBRANCE-DAY15-24x16.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/2022-ARMED-FORCES-REMEMBRANCE-DAY15-36x24.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/2022-ARMED-FORCES-REMEMBRANCE-DAY15-48x32.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /> <img class="alignnone wp-image-650157" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/2022-ARMED-FORCES-REMEMBRANCE-DAY14.jpg" alt="" width="550" height="367" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/2022-ARMED-FORCES-REMEMBRANCE-DAY14.jpg 1080w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/2022-ARMED-FORCES-REMEMBRANCE-DAY14-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/2022-ARMED-FORCES-REMEMBRANCE-DAY14-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.co